raw_data.description: Charlotte Mecklenburg Library is the library system serving Mecklenburg County, NC with 20 locations and a digital online site. Our mission is to improve lives and build a stronger community. We create a community of readers and empower individuals.
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 1.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: My son (going into 4th grade) and I visited for the first time today.  AMAZING! You are truly missing out if you haven't visited this library. Most importantly, the customer service here is outstanding. So good I was genuinely taken back. It only took a moment for a staff member to approach and once I communicated my goal, at least 3 staff members showed interest in assisting! WOW! They make you feel so welcomed and HAPPY TO HELP! LOL You don't feel that way at many places.  HUUUUGE thank you to Victoria for her patience, understanding, deep knowledge, recommendations, and tour of my new favorite place. Y'all made my Monday afternoon! Thank you!

This library is really noisy, it batters me When I'm working.
And their stuff it's terrible. They are rude and like to insult people.

The staff there was very pleasant and cheerful. I easily located the computers in order to print some forms. The staff then was very helpful in setting my forms to print as their printing system is a little old fashioned, but that was not an inconvenience at all. The library was well lit and the set up was very pleasing.
Great library with a wide selection of books and DVD'S! The also have a great writing course the second Saturday every month!
This library is the place to be everyone is so friendly

Staff is friendly and helpful. I couldn't ask for better people when in need. I've had really bad experiences with customer service here in charlotte. But these ladies are definitely a breath of fresh air.
I really love that they have an African American section of fiction books written by and about black people!!
I had been a member for more than 15 years. Since I wasn't active, my library card was expired. I just used my ID to renew.  There were plenty of computers for the public. The limit time is 1 hour.
This library is an amazing place. Not too crowded and always a nice place to be. Love it here.

The lady at the front desk was very rude and loud mouth and she was Hispanic and the lady that was at the second desk was also rude and I she was Muslim because she had something on her head.  But Doug the young black man that helped me with my computer training was very nice and compassion and had a lot of patience. I thought the Library was a place to study but them ladies were very loud talking with each others.
The staff is always friendly and helpful.
Job fair going on today. Charmac 311, CMS and others are there. The library has tons of resources on resume creation and review etc.
Its amazing we get to do small activities with the librarian
Beautiful space and very friendly and helpful staff!

As a volunteer at Independence Regional, I can say that the staff is absolutely the best! Always friendly, welcoming, involved and very knowledgeable. It’s always a pleasure to be there and be a part of the fun!
Clean quiet and nice!
This library is too loud! The patrons and staff are rude and hey talk extremely loudly, carrying on as if they were in a restaurant.

This library unfortunately has gone down since COVID hit I think.
The staff became so dry.
Somethings off about the older African American woman who usually always has an attitude when approached with questions by individuals who are looking for help while she’s sitting behind either help desk.
I’ve observed this so many times. I avoid her at all cost. If she’s the only one there, I just don’t ask any questions.
The staff is always so noisy and I’m unsure if they have a private room for studying or not but since we don’t have internet at home, I’m trying to tutor my kids and do my homework when I can.
Doors should be built on both of the separate children’s room spaces. The fullness of the place kinda makes me depressed now walking in.

The nice nerdy guy with the glasses and orange hair is ALWAYS so helpful and polite. Love asking him for help when we need clarity.
Staff is extremely friendly, the place has a great atmosphere for working.
Great materials and exceptional staff.
I am so happy about the teen programs they have for the kids. It's absolutely amazing the different things that are offered every day after school.
It is a beautiful library!  Make sure to check out the artwork!
Staff was very friendly and helpful.
Always find the books I want. Staff is very pleasant.

The manager who engages in elder abuse also abuses the entire staff and gets off on it. She’s a pathetic, petty human being whose poison is spread through the entire branch. She’s why so many employees have quit that particular library. Her misery is palatable and CML should be ashamed to enable such abusive behavior, but it’s not. The patrons at Independence deserve better.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello, Stephanie. Thank you for your review. We take the concerns mentioned in your review seriously and would like to learn more about these claims. Could you please share additional details about what you've observed or experienced with us directly at ceo@cmlibrary.org. We thank you for the opportunity to investigate and resolve this matter.

reviews_data.review_text: The keyboards in the room with 4 computers need to be cleaned sanatized on a regular basis. Especially during times like this.
The best branch in Charlotte. Friendly professional staff
IT IS ALWAYS A DELIGHT GOING TO INDEPENDENCE REGIONAL LIBRARY. THE STAFF IS ALWAYS WELCOMING AND OFFER TO HELP IN ANY WAY THEY CAN.
I Love going here because the people are so friendly 🙂 and helpful
The purpose of my visit was to use the internet .the staff were superfrieindly .ill definitely return
Great staff
The manager of this library engages in elder abuse. She talks down to her employees, not what I want to hear when I enter a library. Very poor example of the Public Library in Mecklenburg County.
This library is clean quiet and convenient.  I was able to get in and out quickly and take care of the business I needed on their computer.  I also love that they are open until 8pm.
I used the printer and color copier for free!  Picked up some DVDs to watch right before closing. Very convenient!!
The Independence Branch of Charlotte Mecklenburg Public Library is a great place to go. Great staff and good selection!
Friendly and helpful staff!
Wonderful.

We have taken advantage of a few virtual programs for preschoolers/elementary students. Each program has been well thought out and fun for my kiddos! Every visit to this location has been a positive experience. Friendly staff and organized pick ups for kits needed for virtual programs. Thank you!!

From security at entrance to counter staff, everyone was extremely friendly, helpful and very professional.
It was my first visit and I was pleased with my experience and definitely will return when needed.
The lady who answers the phone is so nice

💜 I really miss homeschooling my children at this location. We always made a lot of mommy friends and that is a serious thing that I will miss. Since the Covid situation has happened, socializing has been very hard for my children and I. But anyways, I just wanted to highlight an employee for their bright personality. Even though the world is in the state that it is currently ... I would love to highlight Ms. Erin, because every single time I call in a print or have a question ✋🏾 she answers the phone I know that she will be nothing but pleasant. 💕Thank you for being so sweet. 🤍
I use their FREE WI FI by sitting SAFELY in my car in their parking lot, not worrying about being close to other people.😯😃😎
Excellent service and great facilities

It’s a nice place to go in the morning and the staff is great but after the school let out that’s across the street the kids come in it becomes noisy you will not be able to get your work done it’s very loud and no one says anything to tell the kids it’s a library not a social gathering but overall nice library
Always has info about free events

It's a nice enough library, but if you're actually going for a quiet place to be this is NOT the one to go to. Kids from the school across the street come over and treat it like an afterschool program and it's SO SO LOUD!! The staff does absolutely nothing to help and it's just unbearable. Seriously, something needs to be done. Get a better security guard or something that will actually help the people who come to have a real library experience.

If you are looking for a really library that is on the smaller end of things then you should definitely check out the Charlotte Mecklenburg Library - Independence Regional.   This place has some very cool people working here and the wifi here is great if you don't have intranet.
I've always had superior service at this location!
Great library.  Yet again, what library is bad?  If it has books,  all other things are gravy.

This is a great place I really like it but the only problem I had is that a few girls came by and were talking about inappropriate things and they knew one of the staffs but she did not do anything I am very disappointed but I have to admit I will go back hopefully they take better look at this

One of the ladies of the staff is so loud when she talks and when I told her to please lower her voice, she was very rude to me. It's so sad how people that should be the example to others are leading others in the wrong direction, may God have mercy over this nation! Libraries are not that educational and professional anymore.
The staff is always helpful and pleasant, they smile a lot and greet you acordinly. This is a good place to take a break from the craze in your day and relaxed with a pleasant attidute.

Those kids from the school come over and make a lot of noise. One even stole my sunglasses because I made a reservation to get online, on the same computer he was trying to use. Those kids are a bunch of knuckleheads who have no home training. Because of them they don't allow us to download anything on the computers and you can't even any music videos on YouTube because of those children.
A loud library; good for groups of young students to meet up.
Very nice staff! But  that was the loudest library in America. Even in the quiet section in back of library had people yelling and on the phone. Very weird that the rules aren't enforced.
Loudest library ever... every time I come in here. They have no control over the kids in here.

Nice location staff is all ways friendly. Just watch out when the high school gets out around 2:30 or 3pm weekdays students come over and want to hang out and talk loud while your trying to read and work.
Love This Library!! Very accommodating!! I tutor students and find everything we need!!

This would be a great library if it wasn’t so LOUD IN HERE!!!! What happened to librarians sushing everyone? Every time I come here it’s so unusualy loud for a library. I find people talking loudly on their phones, the kids in the teen area holding court and carrying on as if they are somewhere else and not in the very center of the library, even the librarians shout to one another! I came to the library looking for a quiet place to study and I can’t even hear myself think...
The place is easy to get to and the staff is very helpful and nice.
Helpful staff, great resources and a great space with lots of natural sunlight.

We love this library. They have a great children's department. The family story time (ages 0-5) at 10:30 Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday is fun, interactive and instructive. They do reading, singing and dancing all while teaching. It's a great place to spend a morning with your little ones.
The only thing we don't love is the lack of toys. They have some just not very many.  It would be nice if they got a few more.
Great place to take the kids
Independence regional and the University location are my fav. The staff is always super helpful, the selection is great. If they don't have it they it they will find it

I love this library!! It is an amazing place to study, plus they office 3 hours of validated parking, so what's not to like? My favorite thing are all the windows. A lot of libraries feel like stuffy office buildings with hardly any light, but this library has windows going across at least 2 of the walls so it's usually pretty bright. There are usually plenty of seats and outlets for studying. It's definitely my go to study spot.
有点小
Very polite staff and clean and well kept.
Best library ever!  It's especially great for kids.

Not a pleasant library.  Students from the high school across the street overrun this branch at all times.  The "security" guard just sits up front and ignores everything occurring.  Some students will harass you.
Buena y muy cordial
Awsome go ther every 2 or 3 weeks ther staff is awsome better that any library

I don't like this ghetto library. The staff allow people to do whatever they want. Those rude patrons talk on their phones loudly and play their music loudly and the staff says nothing to them. It's more like a school cafeteria in there than a library. The staff is nice but weak. They don't enforce any of the rules.
The library is like my best friend. I love my Independence branch. Staff is Awesome!!!!

Large sized Library. Cool found rooms throughout.Two computer lab with an additional area with adult and children computers.

Children's area
-Large room for storytime with preschool aged books
- play area with puzzles, toys, other activity's and early reader area.
- large non fiction area
-room with children's fiction books and audio books
-small children's DVD section

Family storytime was nice, but it did seem a bit more geared towards the older children.

The Storyteller was very engaging and entertaining.

Other library staff was very friendly and helpful as well
Really great library, helpful librarians
Good people
Beautiful place to relax and get  whatever  you need done
Love the staff , very helpful and personal.
